column1: #Text=But next month we 're going to launch a big fund raising campaign to get together all the money to do it all .
#Text=Are you going to continue with that ?
#Text=So two weeks , no less than two weeks , the fourteenth of January , we go to the AIS for our first training camp of the Rio campaign .
#Text=So I might be able to catch you guys again there .
#Text=It must have been disappointing in London —
#Text=I 'm watching the game , and it 's " oh no , they 're losing " but you do n't look like you 're losing .
#Text=You look like you 're having the time of your life .
#Text=I mean , what we play for is to play on the world stage and it is a lot of fun .
#Text=Did you see how many people were there was ?
#Text=I was staring up at the top and I could not see the top rows .
#Text=There was so many people there , and they were all supporting us .
#Text=It was the best I 've ever done .
#Text=But yeah , of course it 's disappointing , because you do n't want to win silver , or lose gold , but ...
#Text=Yeah , being second in the world 's pretty good , definitely , but silver 's tough .
#Text=It 's just that the Gliders have never won .
#Text=They 've never won the World Championship , they 've never won at the Paralympics .
#Text=Yeah , so obviously we wanted to change that .
#Text=We did what we were capable of .
#Text=We just were n't quite good enough .
#Text=We had patches where we did n't play well , but that 's basketball .
#Text=The whole team needed to find something and lift , because like ...
#Text=we interviewed one of your team mates , and she we ca n't expect to win if we 're shooting 39 per cent .
#Text=Then of course you went ahead and won two games shooting 39 per cent , which sort of made a bit of a liar out of her ...
